Package: samplyr
Title: A Tidy Grammar for Survey Sampling
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ahmadou", "Dicko", , "mail@ahmadoudicko.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9654-7582"))
Author: Ahmadou Dicko [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Ahmadou Dicko <mail@ahmadoudicko.com>
Description: Provides a tidy, composable grammar for specifying and executing
    complex survey sampling designs. Supports stratified, clustered, multi-stage,
    and multi-phase sampling with a minimal set of verbs that compose naturally.
    Designed to bridge the gap between verbal descriptions of sampling plans
    and executable R code, following tidyverse design principles. Includes
    synthetic survey datasets from African countries (Niger, Uganda, Kenya,
    Tanzania, Nigeria) for learning and testing.
